descriptions: In Quarter Total Attach Rate Progression - Quarterly Comparision

Corporate 15/12 Attach Rate

The 15/12 metric is a standard corporate view for attach rate. 15 months to attach service are divided by 12 months of shipments. The 3 recent months of shipment are not included, as the calculation allows for 90 days beyond the 12 months of shipments to attach services, in order to maximize the attach rate. The 15/12 attach rate is a rolling metric, which means that every time you look at it, you are looking at prior 15 months that align with a given month.

Example- Letâ€™s imagine that we want to inspect the 15/12 attach rate for July FY17. To do that, we need to look at products shipped from May FY16 through April FY 17. The service booking for this timeframe can occur anytime during the 15 month period between May FY16 through July FY17. The last 3-month period (May, June and July of FY 17) provides extra time to attach services for products shipped between May FY17 and April FY17.

Commercial Warranty (Wholesale) â€“ OEM product without end user attributes.
Short Term Warranty â€“ Term limited Warranties that are less than 2 years duration.
Long Term Warranty â€“Term limited Warranties equal or greater than 2 years (currently up to 5 years).
LIFE â€“ Warranties without a fixed term, bounded by EoL process. 5 total types, includes LLW and ELLW Warranties.

Example-
20 items shipped in April FY17.
10 items had Services Attached in 10 days, another 10 items were Attached in 20 days.
Average Days to Attach in April FY17 = 15 days.

tsRenew_overview.title: QTD Weekly Renewal Bookings
tsRenew_overview.description:
For each week within the quarter, you'll see a cumulative bookings progression. Bookings are split into Early, Late, Late in Quarter or Late designations. Trend Line shows previous year bookings

Early - Transaction date of contract renewal occurs in a quarter prior to the quarter when the contract line is scheduled to expire

On-Time - Transaction date of contract renewal occurs within the quarter, either on/before it was scheduled to expire.

Late Within Quarter - Transaction date of contract renewal occurs after the day it expires, but within quarter of expiration

Late - Transaction date of contract renewal occurs any quarter after the contract line expiration quarter

Price - Service Contract Net.

tsRenew_overview.title: Renewal by
descriptions:
Renewal Bookings for a selected quarter are broken down by either Sales Level or top 25 Customers. The Bookings are split into Early, Late, Late in Quarter or Late designations. Trend Line shows previous year bookings

Early: Transaction date of contract renewal occurs in a quarter prior to the quarter when the contract line is scheduled to expire

On-Time: Transaction date of contract renewal occurs within the quarter, either on/before it was scheduled to expire.

Late Within Quarter: Transaction date of contract renewal occurs after the day it expires, but within quarter of expiration

Late: Transaction date of contract renewal occurs any quarter after the contract line expiration quarter

The chart illustrates the opportunity for additional renewals within the selected Quarter. Each Sales Level/Customer opportunity is segmented by Active, Overdue, Expired and Signed.

Active: Contract Lines (Active status) that are expiring within current quarter.

Overdue: Contract Lines expiring within current quarter that are past expiration date, but within 30 days grace period.

Expired: Contract Lines expiring within current quarter that are past expiration date plus 30 days.

Signed: Contract Lines in Signed status that are not Active yet

tsRenew_opportunity.title: Opportunity Overview
tsRenew_opportunity.description:
Displays Renewal opportunities (based on the Total Actionable Opportunity(TAO) definition), segmented by the contract line status. Either Active, Overdue, Expired or Signed.

Active: Contract Lines (Active status) that are expiring within current quarter

Overdue: Contract Lines expiring within current quarter that are past expiration date, but within 30 days grace period

Expired: Contract Lines expiring within current quarter that are past expiration date plus 30 days

Signed: Contract Lines in Signed status that are not Active yet

Timeline: Current quarter, 15 future quarters, 5 past quarters (that are not past LDoS or approaching LDoS in the next 12 months)

Overdue - Contract Lines expiring within current quarter that are past expiration date, but within 30 days grace period_x000D_

Expired - Contract Lines expiring within current quarter that are past expiration date plus 30 days_x000D_

Signed - Contract Lines in Signed status that are not Active yet.
